# Keep project-overview.mdc Up to Date

Whenever you make **any** of the changes listed below, you **must** also update the relevant section(s) in `.cursor/rules/project-overview.mdc` **in the same session**, before finishing your response.

## Triggers — update the docs when you:

- **Add, rename, or delete** a service, component, directive, pipe, or guard
- **Add, rename, or delete** a route or change its path / guard
- **Add or remove** a domain model, interface, or type
- **Add or rename** a storage key (Capacitor Preferences, localStorage, sessionStorage)
- **Add or remove** an environment variable (e.g. in `environment.ts` / `environment.prod.ts`)
- **Add or remove** a Capacitor plugin or any `package.json` dependency that changes the stack
- **Move or restructure** a folder that is listed in the Directory layout section
- **Resolve** one of the listed "Known caveats / tech debt" items
- **Introduce** a new noteworthy caveat or architectural decision

## What to update

Match the trigger to the section in `project-overview.mdc`:

| Trigger | Section to update |
|---|---|
| Service change | **Services** table |
| Component / directive change | **Shared components** table |
| Route change | **Routing** block |
| Model / interface change | **Domain models** block |
| Storage key change | **Storage keys** table |
| Environment variable change | **External APIs** or **Environment** note |
| Capacitor plugin change | **Capacitor plugins in use** list |
| Dependency / stack change | **Stack** table |
| Folder restructure | **Directory layout** tree |
| Caveat resolved or added | **Known caveats / tech debt** list |

## How to update

1. Open `.cursor/rules/project-overview.mdc`.
2. Find the matching section using the table above.
3. Edit only that section — keep every other section intact.
4. Do **not** rewrite unrelated sections or change the file structure.
5. Confirm the update in your response so the user knows the docs were kept in sync.
